nsumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20legitimate%20concerns%20that%20this%20influx%20of%20capital%20into%20the%20US%20will%20increase%20liquidity%2C%20driving%20up%20asset%20prices%20and%20inflationary%20pressure%2C%20making%20it%20more%20challenging%20for%20the%20Fed%20to%20lower%20rates%2C%26quot%3B%20Green%20said.%20%26quot%3BIncreased%20liquidity%20can%20lead%20to%20inflationary%20pressures%2C%20which%20the%20Fed%20might%20need%20to%20counteract%20by%20maintaining%20or%20even%20raising%20rates.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Green%20mentioned%2C%20there's%20a%20way%20for%20the%20Fed%20to%20fight%20back%3A%20hiking%20interest%20rates%20some%20more.%20But%20jacking%20up%20interest%20rates%20even%20further%20could%20finally%20break%20the%20back%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-outlook-hard-landing-economy-consumer-spending-slowdown-growth-gdp-2024-5%23%3A~%3Atext%3DConsumers%2520are%2520finally%2520slowing%2520their%2Cand%2520a%2520weakening%2520job%2520market.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euntil%20now%20strong%20US%20consumer%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20send%20us%20into%20a%20recession.%20It's%20the%20same%20calculation%20the%20ECB%20is%20making%2C%20though%20the%20EU's%20slowdown%20is%20more%20marked.%20Given%20these%20downsides%2C%20the%20Fed%20is%20unlikely%20to%20hike%2C%20which%20will%20create%20the%20perfect%20market%20for%20the%20carry%20trade%20to%20thrive.%20And%20as%20long%20as%20US%20data%20remains%20choppy%20%E2%80%94%20pointing%20to%20sticky%20inflation%20one%20day%20and%20disinflation%20the%20next%20%E2%80%94%20this%20carry-trade%20cash%20will%20end%20up%20sloshing%20around%20in%20the%20economy.%20This%20is%20a%20dynamic%20that%20central%20banks%20from%20countries%20already%20on%20their%20rate-cutting%20path%20will%20be%20watching.%20They're%20already%20seeing%20growth%20slow%20and%2C%20on%20top%20of%20that%2C%20will%20have%20money%20sucked%20away%20to%20the%20US%2C%20where%20data%20has%20been%20relatively%20strong%20through%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%20year.%20Carry-trade%20cash%20exploits%20the%20dislocations%20between%20global%20economies%20that%20are%20keeping%20our%20policies%20from%20coordinating.%20We're%20in%20the%20early%20innings%2C%20but%20the%20longer%20this%20goes%20on%2C%20the%20more%20of%20an%20impact%20it%20will%20make.%20For%20Wall%20Street%2C%20that%20means%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-summer-worry-stock-market-crash-inflation-hamtons-vacation-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20summer%20of%20vigilance%3C%2Fa%3E.%20For%20economists%2C%20it%20means%20the%20picture%20of%20our%20economy%20that%20they're%20trying%20to%20cobble%20together%20with%20contradictory%20data%20is%20even%20blurrier.%20It's%20a%20time%20of%20increased%20uncertainty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESticky-ing%20the%20landing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20hope%20that%20this%20divergence%20will%20be%20only%20a%20temporary%20state%20of%20affairs.%20If%20the%20US%20suddenly%20starts%20printing%20weak%20economic%20data%2C%20that%20will%20hasten%20the%20Fed's%20move%20to%20cut%20rates.%20And%20there%20are%20signs%20that%20EU%20inflation%20is%20stickier%20than%20policymakers%20would%20like%2C%20which%20could%20slow%20the%20pace%20of%20cuts%20enough%20for%20America%20to%20catch%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20already%20signs%20of%20a%20slight%20tempering%20of%20America's%20red-hot%20economy%3A%20The%20household%20savings%20rate%20is%20at%20a%2016-month%20low%2C%20disposable%20incomes%20have%20made%20only%20modest%20gains%2C%20and%20the%20amount%20that%20people%20have%20to%20pay%20on%20credit%20balances%20is%20elevated.%20The%20white-hot%20job%20market%20has%20cooled%2C%20and%20job%20openings%20have%20returned%20to%20prepandemic%20levels.%20But%20not%20every%20indicator%20is%20telling%20the%20story%20of%20a%20soft%20landing.%20On%20Friday%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-unemployment-rate-job-growth-looked-in-may-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMay's%20jobs%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%20that%20the%20country%20created%20272%2C000%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20way%20more%20than%20the%20182%2C000%20expected.%20The%20data%20seesaw%20stateside%20continues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20Atlantic%2C%20there%20are%20signs%20that%20UK%20and%20EU%20inflation%20could%20be%20stickier%20than%20policymakers%20had%20foreseen.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Finterestrates%2Feurozone-inflation-rises-ahead-of-ecb-meeting-1033440963%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEU%20inflation%20ticked%20up%20slightly%20to%202.6%25%20in%20May%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20surprising%20the%20ECB%20but%20not%20shocking%20it%20enough%20to%20stop%20a%20June%20rate%20cut.%20In%20the%20UK%2C%20stubborn%20services%20inflation%2C%20which%20came%20in%20at%205.9%25%20for%20the%20month%20of%20April%2C%20may%20give%20the%20Bank%20of%20England%20reason%20to%20pause.%20Oxford%20Economics'%20Basic%20Vasiljev%20told%20me%20that%20this%20indicated%20that%20the%20EU%20and%20US%20were%20moving%20more%20in%20tandem%20than%20this%20policy%20lag%20suggests%20and%20the%20current%20policy%20divergence%20would%20remain%20short.%20Even%20the%20Bank%20of%20Canada%2C%20which%20cut%20its%20benchmark%20rate%20to%204.75%25%20from%205%25%20last%20week%2C%20is%20cautiously%20optimistic%20the%20dislocation%20will%20be%20momentary.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20limits%20to%20how%20far%20we%20can%20diverge%20from%20the%20United%20States%2C%20but%20we're%20not%20close%20to%20those%20limits%2C%26quot%3B%20Gov.%20Tiff%20Macklem%20said%20at%20the%20Bank%20of%20Canada's%20latest%20meeting.%20Not%20close%E2%80%A6%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20rosy%20outlook%20is%20not%20a%20guarantee%3A%20Wall%20Street%20still%20expects%20three%20cuts%20this%20year%20from%20the%20ECB%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Feuropean-shares-fall-amid-data-deluge-1033460481%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBank%20of%20England%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Even%20in%20little%20clips%20of%200.25%25%2C%20three%20cuts%20would%20create%20a%20divergence%20traders%20would%20exploit.%20And%20if%20September%20comes%20and%20the%20US%20is%20still%20hot%2C%20that%20exploitation%20could%20continue%20all%20year%20long%2C%20exacerbating%20the%20conditions%20that%20are%20keeping%20monetary%20policy%20out%20of%20sync.%20That%20sucking%20sound%20you'll%20hear%20all%20summer%20is%20the%20sound%20of%20Wall%20Street%20slurping%20money%20from%20Europe%2C%20Canada%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20and%20East%20Asia%20into%20US%20markets.%20Policymakers%20will%20have%20to%20recalibrate.%20This%20doesn't%20mean%20we%20won't%20stick%20a%20soft%20landing%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20if%20this%20disordered%20moment%20is%20brief%20%E2%80%94%20it%20just%20increases%20the%20odds%20of%20a%20bumpy%20ride%20until%20we%20get%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Flinette-lopez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ELinette%20Lopez%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-economy-recession-stock-market-crash-inflation-interest-rates-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717926421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66634178ed9a404d829bbfaf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-economy-recession-stock-market-crash-inflation-interest-rates-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There's%20a%20growing%20gap%20between%20America's%20interest%20rates%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%20That's%20going%20to%20cause%20some%20problems.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22llopez%40insider.com%20(Linette%20Lopez)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-economy-recession-stock-market-crash-inflation-interest-rates-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20boomer%20couple%20who%20retired%20early%20to%20Colombia%20explains%20their%20'exit%20strategy'%20and%20how%20much%20they%20now%20pay%20in%20monthly%20expenses%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22753%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22John%20and%20Susan%20Pazera%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6661b9cdd0b8e1c832cc744d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22565%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJohn%20and%20Susan%20Pazera%20left%20the%20US%20and%20retired%20in%20Colombia.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20John%20and%20Susan%20Pazera%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJohn%20and%20Susan%20Pazera%20moved%20to%20Colombia%20six%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20knew%20they%20wanted%20to%20retire%20early%2C%20and%20they%20saw%20leaving%20the%20US%20as%20the%20only%20way%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETheir%20expenses%20in%20Colombia%20are%20low%2C%20and%20the%20affordable%20healthcare%20makes%20a%20big%20difference.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20and%20Susan%20Pazera%20knew%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeak-boomer-scared-to-retire-working-depleted-savings-social-security-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirement%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20look%20a%20lot%20different%20if%20they%20chose%20to%20stay%20in%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20sailors%2C%20John%20and%20Susan%20%E2%80%94%C2%A068%20and%2064%2C%20respectively%20%E2%80%94%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flatitudeadjustmentblog.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eno%20strangers%20to%20travel%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%202001%2C%20the%20couple%20took%20a%20three-year%20sabbatical%20and%20sailed%20down%20the%20West%20Coast%20to%20Central%20America%2C%20where%20they%20stopped%20in%20Panama.%20It%20was%20a%20moment%20of%20inspiration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20started%20getting%20us%20to%20think%20that%20maybe%20we%20could%20retire%20at%20a%20younger%20age%20if%20we%20moved%20outside%20the%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey're%20not%20the%20only%20retirees%20to%20make%20the%20leap.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBI%20has%20previously%20spoken%20to%20a%20range%20of%20Americans%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-portugal-boomer-couple-retirement-not-worried-about-money-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewho%20chose%20to%20move%20abroad%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20seek%20better%20and%20more%20affordable%20conditions%20in%20retirement.%20For%20many%20older%20Americans%2C%20it%20can%20solidify%20their%20financial%20security%20later%20in%20life%2C%20especially%20because%20just%20over%20half%20of%20people%20over%2065%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-crisis-social-security-poverty-older-americans-savings-inequality-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20they%20made%20%2430%2C000%20or%20less%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202022%20while%20in%20the%20US%2C%20per%20the%20Census%20Bureau's%20Current%20Population%20Survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoving%20to%20a%20new%20country%20can%20certainly%20present%20challenges%2C%20including%20the%20political%20atmosphere%20and%20potential%20language%20barriers.%20John%20and%20Susan%20recommended%20that%20anyone%20seeking%20to%20move%20abroad%20visit%20the%20place%20they%20might%20want%20to%20live%20a%20few%20times%2C%20especially%20when%20it's%20not%20tourist%20season%20and%20the%20weather%20is%20not%20as%20nice.%20They%20also%20suggested%20waiting%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20before%20purchasing%20any%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20adapt%20to%20that%20country's%20culture%20and%20lifestyle.%20You%20can't%20bring%20your%20US%20mentality%20to%20another%20country%20and%20expect%20everything%20to%20be%20the%20same%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20wipe%20clean%20everything%20that%20you%20expect%20from%20the%20US%20that%20you%20think%20you're%20going%20to%20get%20from%20another%20country.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22887b5fb3-70d2-4799-a899-4e3e4e17a4a3%5C%22%3EHow%20they%20made%20the%20move%20and%20what%20life%20costs%20in%20Colombia%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20John%20and%20Susan%20started%20planning%2C%20they%20first%20focused%20on%20boosting%20their%20savings.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThen%2C%20in%202015%2C%20they%20sold%20their%20house%20and%20cars%20packed%20everything%20away%20in%20seven%20duffel%20bags%20and%20moved%20to%20Panama%20with%20their%20two%20dogs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20ultimately%20decided%20that%20Panama%20wasn't%20the%20right%20fit.%20Having%20already%20visited%20some%20cities%20in%20Colombia%2C%20they%20were%20familiar%20with%20the%20lifestyle%20there%20and%20felt%20confident%20making%20it%20their%20new%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20said%20that%20had%20they%20not%20moved%20abroad%2C%20early%20retirement%20would%20not%20have%20been%20a%20possibility.%20Instead%2C%20they%20both%20retired%20at%2059%20%E2%80%94%20Susan%20worked%20remotely%20for%20a%20few%20years.%20That's%20compared%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.empower.com%2Fthe-currency%2Flife%2Fwhat-is-the-average-retirement-age%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20the%20average%20retirement%20age%20%3C%2Fa%3Eof%2063%20for%20women%20and%2065%20for%20men%20in%20the%20US.%20Plus%2C%20they%20believe%20their%20quality%20of%20life%20after%20retirement%20is%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverything%20was%20just%20so%20expensive%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20we%20were%20able%20to%20afford%20it%2C%20but%20it's%20like%2C%20do%20we%20want%20to%20have%20this%20lifestyle%20until%20we%20retire%3F%20We%20got%20to%20figure%20out%20an%20exit%20strategy%20to%20get%20out%20quicker.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20recently%20purchased%20property%20outside%20of%20Medell%C3%ADn%2C%20Colombia%2C%20so%20they%20no%20longer%20have%20rent%20payments%2C%20but%20they%20estimate%20they'll%20owe%20around%20%24137%20a%20month%20in%20apartment%20insurance%20and%20property%20taxes.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20their%20basic%20monthly%20expenses%2C%20they%20spend%20about%20%2445%20a%20month%20on%20utilities%2C%20%2440%20a%20month%20on%20cell%20phones%2C%20and%20%2436%20a%20month%20on%20internet.%20Healthcare%20costs%20vary%20each%20month%2C%20but%20they%20said%20it's%20typically%20around%20%24300.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20couple%20said%20that%20moving%20also%20gave%20them%20the%20peace%20of%20mind%20of%20knowing%20that%20as%20they%20age%2C%20they'll%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretired-americans-move-to-italy-affordable-healthcare-work-life-balance-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20healthcare%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20can%20rely%20on%20for%20any%20physical%20ailments%20they%20might%20face.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20stay%20in%20the%20US%2C%20one%20of%20us%20gets%20really%2C%20really%20sick%20with%20some%20strange%20disease%2C%20and%20the%20insurance%20company%20says%2C%20'Well%2C%20we%20don't%20cover%20that.'%20And%20then%20it's%20all%20out%20of%20your%20pocket%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20all%20the%20money%20you%20saved%20your%20whole%20life%2C%20you%20have%20to%20dip%20into%20your%20savings%20for%20something%20that's%20not%20covered%20by%20the%20health%20insurance%20companies.%20But%20here%2C%20we%20know%20we%20can%20get%20sick%20with%20anything%20in%20the%20world%2C%20and%20we're%20going%20to%20be%20taken%20care%20of.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flatitudeadjustmentblog.com%2F2023%2F12%2F15%2Fhealthcare-in-colombia-our-experience%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enot%20free%20healthcare%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Susan%20emphasized%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bit's%20really%20eye-opening%26quot%3B%20to%20see%20the%20quality%20of%20care%20she%20can%20get%20in%20Colombia%20for%20a%20significantly%20lower%20price%20than%20she%20could%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELower%20healthcare%20costs%20are%20often%20a%20key%20reason%20people%20might%20choose%20to%20leave%20the%20US.%20Another%20expat%2C%20Debra%20Crockett%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-security-checks-enough-for-retirement-expenses-turkey-cheaper-lifestyle-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20BI%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20she%20moved%20to%20Turkey%20after%20battling%20high%20health%20expenses%20in%20the%20US%20and%20found%20the%20situation%20to%20be%20much%20more%20affordable%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20and%20Susan%20are%20grateful%20that%20finances%20are%20not%20a%20concern%20for%20them%20as%20they%20continue%20to%20live%20abroad%20in%20retirement.%20But%20it's%20more%20than%20that%20%E2%80%94%20they%20said%20their%20neighborhood%20is%20very%20walkable%2C%20they're%20able%20to%20do%20a%20range%20of%20outdoor%20activities%20like%20hiking%20and%20biking%2C%20and%20their%20neighborhood%20frequently%20has%20cultural%20events%20and%20activities%20they%20can%20participate%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20achieved%20their%20goal%20of%20early%20retirement%2C%20and%20now%20they%20can%20enjoy%20the%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20easy%20all%20the%20time%2C%20but%20it's%20forced%20us%20to%20get%20out%20into%20the%20community%20and%20learn%20because%20it's%20complete%20immersion%2C%26quot%3B%20Susan%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20it%20really%20feels%20like%20the%20place%20we%20are%20meant%20to%20be%20at%20this%20point%20in%20time.%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHow%20are%20you%20planning%20for%20retirement%3F%20Share%20your%20story%20with%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aasheffey%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target